etymology.description: 𠬞 is a variant form of 拱(拱) (gǒng, "to cup hands") -> Ideogrammic: 扌(扌) (shǒu, "hand") + phonetic 共(共) (gòng, "together")
etymology.interpretation: 𠬞 is an alternative form of 拱(拱) (gǒng, "to cup hands") and similarly represents two hands coming together, using 扌(扌) (shǒu, "hand") for the semantic component and 共(共) (gòng, "together") for the phonetic similarity.
